        ﾂｧl Book II
ﾂｧr
  The Trials of Being
     a Missionary


-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
#- In providing the world
with the Book of Beret,
 I have seen the trial
      of this world
    and the troubles
     that come with
  spreading the word.

          Roads
  are not far spread,
 and rails are clogged
       with obsidian
  from wars long past.
#-  

 Few will see the word,
  and less will choose
         to care.

        But, even
     with all of this
 piling against we who
   spread the word
       of Beretism,
  we must perservere.
#- 


     Glorious is he
who spreads the word,
   even in the face
    of adversaries
    and challanges
      such as that
      that populate
        our world.
#- 

 Find solace
  in the fact
   that you have
    spreadthe word,
     and helped others
       reach    
        enlightenment
         in the name
          of Redberet.

#-          Don
   your red caps
  with pride, knowing       that it is a pure
   and noble cause.

         Do not
   feel threatened
     when people
  persecute you in
  His name, for His
 armies are more than    can be fathomed
      in this world.
#-  
‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾

  So, spread the word
        my friends,
    and help all other
       people know
    the truth that is
       the Kingdom
       of Redberet

+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+‾+
#- 
